the aim of this study was to estimate the dietary cadmium cd intake of the belgian adult population to compare this dietary cd exposure to the tolerable weekly intake twi recently established by the european food safety authority efsa and to determine the major food groups that contribute to dietary cd exposure in belgiumfood consumption data were derived from the 2004 belgian food consumption survey two 24 h recalls 3083 participantscadmium concentrations in food items n  4000 were gathered from the control program of the belgian federal agency for the safety of the food chain for the period 20062008dietary intake per individual was calculated from consumption data and median cd concentrationsthe population mean median and 95th percentile of the dietary intake values were 098 085 and 202 µg kg¹ body weight per week respectivelytwo percent of the belgian adult population has a dietary cd intake above the recent twi of 25 µg kg¹ body weight established by efsa in 2009cereal products and potatoes contribute for more than 60 to cd intake